properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 14 at 9:28PM MST until January 15 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...ANOTHER ROUND OF STRONG GUSTY WINDS LIKELY TONIGHT THROUGH
EARLY WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 2 PM MST Wednesday. The High
Wind Watch is no longer in effect.

* TIMING...Overnight tonight through early Wednesday afternoon.

* WINDS...West to northwest between 30 to 45 mph with occasional
gusts up to 65 mph.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds may
create dangerous travel conditions. There is a high blow-over
risk for light and high profile vehicles, including campers
and tractor trailers.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST WEDNESDAY
